headline: MicroStrategy's bitcoin-powered surge takes it closer to Nasdaq 100 doorstep
summary: A meteoric rise in MicroStrategy's shares has made the bitcoin hoarder a likely candidate for the tech-heavy Nasdaq 100 index ahead of an annual reshuffle this week.  The loss-making software company, an aggressive investor in the highly volatile cryptocurrency, has seen its shares soar nearly 500% this year, taking its market capitalization to $90 billion.  It got a big boost after Donald Trump's U.S. election victory as investors expect the president-elect to make good on his promise of a crypto-friendly administration.
